1
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:03,733
[♪]

2
00:01:01,666 --> 00:01:03,566
[PANTING]

3
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:06,166
Miss Hannah,
what's the hurry?

4
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:09,700
Jake's in the garden.

5
00:01:09,733 --> 00:01:11,566
Miss Hannah, wait!

6
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:13,266
Oh! I hope her father
doesn't find out.

7
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:20,733
Jake!

8
00:01:20,766 --> 00:01:22,600
Hey, Jake!

9
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:23,766
Oh.

10
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,766
Good afternoon,
Miss Hannah.

11
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:28,100
I want to help you
water the flowers.

12
00:01:28,133 --> 00:01:29,066
Please, do not--
It's okay.

13
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:30,266
Oh.

14
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:32,666
Look at all
the pretty flowers.

15
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:35,266
I wish I could spend all day
in the garden with you, Jake.

16
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:36,533
Do not neglect
these flowers over here.

17
00:01:36,566 --> 00:01:37,733
Okay.

18
00:01:37,766 --> 00:01:39,733
Thank you for helping today.

19
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:41,733
What is going on here?
Huh?

20
00:01:41,766 --> 00:01:43,533
JAKE:
Oh! General!

21
00:01:43,566 --> 00:01:45,700
How many times
do I have to tell you

22
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:46,766
to stay away from
my daughter?

23
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:48,600
I am sorry, sir.

24
00:01:48,633 --> 00:01:49,700
No, Father.

25
00:01:49,733 --> 00:01:51,533
I wanted to help Jake
in the garden.

26
00:01:51,566 --> 00:01:53,733
Robots are not
your friends, Hannah.

27
00:01:53,766 --> 00:01:55,366
They are not like
you and me.

28
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:57,600
They are only tools
that work for humans

29
00:01:57,633 --> 00:01:58,666
and nothing more.

30
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:01,333
Jake is not
a tool, Father.

31
00:02:01,366 --> 00:02:04,100
He is my friend,
and he keeps me company.

32
00:02:04,133 --> 00:02:06,300
He's here for me
whenever I'm lonely,

33
00:02:06,333 --> 00:02:07,633
much more
than you ever are.

34
00:02:07,666 --> 00:02:08,633
[GASPS]

35
00:02:08,666 --> 00:02:11,233
Oh!

36
00:02:11,266 --> 00:02:14,233
FEMALE BUTLER:
Oh, general, you're home!

37
00:02:14,266 --> 00:02:16,233
Take Hannah
into the house.

38
00:02:16,266 --> 00:02:18,200
Yes, sir. Come on--
No! I don't want to!

39
00:02:18,233 --> 00:02:21,066
HANNAH:
I want to stay with Jake!

40
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:22,533
Father, don't
blame Jake, please!

41
00:02:22,566 --> 00:02:24,500
I see that
in spite of my orders,

42
00:02:24,533 --> 00:02:25,700
you still spend time
with Hannah.

43
00:02:25,733 --> 00:02:27,133
Please, sir--

44
00:02:27,166 --> 00:02:28,533
But that all ends now.

45
00:02:28,566 --> 00:02:30,533
Tomorrow you will start
your new job

46
00:02:30,566 --> 00:02:32,766
at the Waste Disposal
Treatment Center.

47
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,333
Pack up your belongings
and leave this house tonight!

48
00:02:37,066 --> 00:02:38,233
Yes, sir.

49
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:49,633
Goodbye, Miss Hannah,
my friend.

50
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:53,566
Jake!

51
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:54,800
Miss Hannah.

52
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:57,366
Where are you going?

53
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,366
[GASPS]

54
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,800
What's this flower for?

55
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:02,666
From now on, you will
take care of it for me.

56
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:04,600
It's my father.

57
00:03:04,633 --> 00:03:06,766
He ordered you
to leave, didn't he?

58
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,333
I'm sorry.

59
00:03:08,366 --> 00:03:10,066
I'm going to talk to him.
Miss Hannah!

60
00:03:10,100 --> 00:03:12,066
Miss Hannah,
please wait!

61
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:14,033
Don't do this!

62
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:18,400
Aaah...!

63
00:03:18,433 --> 00:03:19,566
Miss Hannah!

64
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:20,733
Aaah!

65
00:03:23,133 --> 00:03:25,200
What's going on?

66
00:03:25,233 --> 00:03:26,433
[GASPS]

67
00:03:26,466 --> 00:03:27,600
Hannah!

68
00:03:27,633 --> 00:03:29,333
Hannah! Hannah!

69
00:03:29,366 --> 00:03:30,500
Wake up!
Ugh...

70
00:03:30,533 --> 00:03:32,200
Why won't she
wake up?

71
00:03:32,233 --> 00:03:33,433
Miss Hannah.

72
00:03:33,466 --> 00:03:34,600
[GRUNTS]

73
00:03:34,633 --> 00:03:36,033
GENERAL:
Jake!

74
00:03:36,066 --> 00:03:38,133
What have you done?

75
00:03:38,166 --> 00:03:39,200
But, sir, I didn't--

76
00:03:39,233 --> 00:03:40,333
Stay away,
robot!

77
00:03:40,366 --> 00:03:42,600
You've done enough
already.

78
00:03:42,633 --> 00:03:46,433
But-- But, sir, it was
just an accident, sir.

79
00:03:46,466 --> 00:03:48,700
GENERAL:
Hannah! Hannah!

80
00:03:53,965 --> 00:03:55,331
NEWSCASTER:
<i>Last night, a young girl</i>
<i>was injured</i>

81
00:03:55,365 --> 00:03:57,165
<i>at the hands of</i>
<i>a GP-IV model robot.</i>

82
00:03:57,198 --> 00:03:59,265
Hmm.

83
00:03:59,298 --> 00:04:01,398
<i>The girl has been identified</i>
<i>as the daughter</i>

84
00:04:01,431 --> 00:04:03,231
<i>of General William Red,</i>
<i>a high-ranking member</i>

85
00:04:03,265 --> 00:04:04,265
<i>of the Metro City</i>
<i>Armed Forces.</i>

86
00:04:04,298 --> 00:04:05,098
Doctor--

87
00:04:05,131 --> 00:04:07,198
This must be
some kind of mistake.

88
00:04:07,231 --> 00:04:09,765
The GP-IV model robot suspect,
<i>known as Jake,</i>

89
00:04:09,798 --> 00:04:11,465
<i>worked for the general</i>
<i>at his home</i>

90
00:04:11,498 --> 00:04:13,265
<i>for the past</i>
<i>two and a half years.</i>

91
00:04:13,298 --> 00:04:15,331
<i>According to hospital reports,</i>
<i>the young girl</i>

92
00:04:15,365 --> 00:04:17,031
<i>is still unconscious</i>
<i>but in stable condition.</i>

93
00:04:17,065 --> 00:04:18,831
Oh, that is
just terrible.

94
00:04:18,865 --> 00:04:21,298
Robots should never be
trusted with children.

95
00:04:21,331 --> 00:04:24,198
Dr. O'Shay asked me to organize
the data on GP-IV robots,

96
00:04:24,231 --> 00:04:25,798
but where
do I begin?

97
00:04:25,831 --> 00:04:27,298
Miss Yuko!

98
00:04:27,331 --> 00:04:29,098
Reno, I take it
you saw the news?

99
00:04:29,131 --> 00:04:31,098
There's no way that robot
attacked a human.

100
00:04:31,131 --> 00:04:32,798
It's against
his programming.

101
00:04:32,831 --> 00:04:35,365
I know. Dr. O'Shay and Astro
are looking into it.

102
00:04:35,398 --> 00:04:36,198
I'm going too.

103
00:04:36,231 --> 00:04:37,698
Reno!

104
00:04:37,731 --> 00:04:40,398
DR. O'SHAY:
Detective, I insist

105
00:04:40,431 --> 00:04:42,398
you check these accusations
thoroughly.

106
00:04:42,431 --> 00:04:44,031
Don't worry, O'Shay.
I'm on it.

107
00:04:44,065 --> 00:04:45,365
Jake's upset.

108
00:04:45,398 --> 00:04:47,865
I'd wait until he calms down
before you talk to him.

109
00:04:47,898 --> 00:04:49,698
Don't tell me
how to do my job.

110
00:04:49,731 --> 00:04:50,698
MAN:
Detective Tawashi.

111
00:04:50,731 --> 00:04:51,898
BOTH:
Huh?

112
00:04:51,931 --> 00:04:53,798
DR. O'SHAY:
Chairman Lyon?

113
00:04:53,831 --> 00:04:55,798
What are you doing here?

114
00:04:55,831 --> 00:04:57,131
Don't tell me--

115
00:04:57,165 --> 00:04:58,798
There will be
a formal hearing

116
00:04:58,831 --> 00:05:00,265
at the Federal Council
this afternoon

117
00:05:00,298 --> 00:05:01,865
regarding this incident.

118
00:05:01,898 --> 00:05:03,265
Formal hearing?

119
00:05:03,298 --> 00:05:04,331
That's right.

120
00:05:04,365 --> 00:05:06,231
We believe a public hearing

121
00:05:06,265 --> 00:05:08,698
would be the best course
of action in this matter.

122
00:05:08,731 --> 00:05:10,298
But I'm in the middle
of my investigation.

123
00:05:10,331 --> 00:05:11,965
A waste of time,
detective.

124
00:05:11,998 --> 00:05:13,931
Jake has already been entrusted
to the Council's care.

125
00:05:13,965 --> 00:05:14,731
REPORTERS:
Chairman Lyon, Mr. Drake--

126
00:05:14,765 --> 00:05:17,131
Oh, no.

127
00:05:17,165 --> 00:05:18,331
REPORTER:
This is the first time

128
00:05:18,365 --> 00:05:19,731
a robot will be put on trial.

129
00:05:19,765 --> 00:05:21,231
How will it be conducted?

130
00:05:21,265 --> 00:05:23,131
Naturally, it'll be a fair
and objective trial,

131
00:05:23,165 --> 00:05:26,898
even if he is just a robot.

132
00:05:27,965 --> 00:05:30,298
MAN:
This is outrageous.

133
00:05:30,331 --> 00:05:32,431
Get back!
Get back!

134
00:05:32,465 --> 00:05:34,331
[CROWD SHOUTING]

135
00:05:34,365 --> 00:05:36,198
Grrr. Jake!

136
00:05:36,231 --> 00:05:38,298
Jake!
Reno!

137
00:05:38,331 --> 00:05:40,331
You didn't really
hurt Hannah, did you?

138
00:05:40,365 --> 00:05:41,865
Gotcha!
Leave me alone!

139
00:05:41,898 --> 00:05:43,165
But I would never
hurt her.

140
00:05:43,198 --> 00:05:44,165
POLICEMAN:
Keep moving.

141
00:05:44,198 --> 00:05:46,098
Tell me,
how is Miss Hannah?

142
00:05:46,131 --> 00:05:48,765
Has she woken up yet?

143
00:05:52,365 --> 00:05:53,798
Reno!

144
00:05:53,831 --> 00:05:56,031
Astro, Jake's
telling the truth.

145
00:05:56,065 --> 00:05:57,998
I am positive
he didn't hurt Hannah.

146
00:05:58,031 --> 00:05:59,898
I believe him too.

147
00:06:02,965 --> 00:06:05,265
GENERAL:
Hannah, open your eyes.

148
00:06:05,298 --> 00:06:06,798
General Red.

149
00:06:06,831 --> 00:06:08,398
Mr. Drake,
Chairman Lyon.

150
00:06:08,431 --> 00:06:10,031
I hope you don't mind,

151
00:06:10,065 --> 00:06:11,831
but we thought
it would be a good idea

152
00:06:11,865 --> 00:06:13,231
to see your daughter
with our own eyes

153
00:06:13,265 --> 00:06:14,431
before the trial begins
this afternoon.

154
00:06:14,465 --> 00:06:15,865
Um--

155
00:06:15,898 --> 00:06:17,165
General, has her condition
improved at all?

156
00:06:17,198 --> 00:06:19,265
I'm afraid not,
and the doctors aren't sure

157
00:06:19,298 --> 00:06:21,465
how much she'll remember
once she wakes up.

158
00:06:21,498 --> 00:06:23,931
DRAKE:
And, of course,
there is the possibility

159
00:06:23,965 --> 00:06:26,331
that she will remain
in a coma forever.

160
00:06:26,365 --> 00:06:28,931
If that happens,
I don't know what I'll do.

161
00:06:28,965 --> 00:06:31,165
You see,
this is my fault.

162
00:06:31,198 --> 00:06:34,831
I brought that miserable robot
into my home.

163
00:06:34,865 --> 00:06:37,165
CHAIRMAN LYON:
General...

164
00:06:37,198 --> 00:06:40,131
I will make sure Jake gets
suitable punishment

165
00:06:40,165 --> 00:06:41,798
for what he has done
to your daughter.

166
00:06:41,831 --> 00:06:43,165
I promise.

167
00:06:43,198 --> 00:06:43,931
Thank you.

168
00:06:47,465 --> 00:06:49,231
[♪]

169
00:06:49,265 --> 00:06:51,698
After reviewing
the evidence presented today,

170
00:06:51,731 --> 00:06:53,431
we believe that Jake
did not want to be transferred

171
00:06:53,465 --> 00:06:55,198
to a new job,

172
00:06:55,231 --> 00:06:57,098
and he intentionally hurt
the general's daughter

173
00:06:57,131 --> 00:06:58,798
in an act of vengeance!

174
00:06:58,831 --> 00:07:00,231
DR. O'SHAY:
Wait! Mr. Chairman!

175
00:07:00,265 --> 00:07:02,365
You must allow Jake
to speak for himself.

176
00:07:02,398 --> 00:07:04,098
The GP-IV model robot

177
00:07:04,131 --> 00:07:05,798
possesses advanced
emotional capabilities.

178
00:07:05,831 --> 00:07:07,165
COUNCILWOMAN:
Objection!

179
00:07:07,198 --> 00:07:09,898
If he possesses
advanced emotional capabilities,

180
00:07:09,931 --> 00:07:11,265
he also possesses
the ability to lie.

181
00:07:11,298 --> 00:07:12,698
How can we trust
anything he says?

182
00:07:12,731 --> 00:07:14,331
Doctor!

183
00:07:16,865 --> 00:07:20,065
This court has found that there
is not one shred of evidence

184
00:07:20,098 --> 00:07:21,698
that proves
Jake's innocence.

185
00:07:21,731 --> 00:07:23,831
For the sake of
our peaceful society,

186
00:07:23,865 --> 00:07:26,331
we must remove all robots
with violent tendencies

187
00:07:26,365 --> 00:07:27,965
from our communities.

188
00:07:27,998 --> 00:07:30,398
The court hereby sentences Jake
to be fully dismantled.

189
00:07:30,431 --> 00:07:32,131
BOTH: Huh!
Huh?

190
00:07:32,165 --> 00:07:35,231
[COUNCIL MEMBERS APPLAUD]

191
00:07:36,898 --> 00:07:38,298
MALE NEWSCASTER:
<i>Well, there you have it.</i>

192
00:07:38,331 --> 00:07:41,865
<i>This historic trial</i>
<i>has come to an end.</i>

193
00:07:43,198 --> 00:07:46,931
So this is
what humans call justice.

194
00:07:53,398 --> 00:07:56,165
REPORTERS:
Chairman Lyon! Chairman Lyon!

195
00:07:56,198 --> 00:07:58,465
Do you have anything to say
about today's decision?

196
00:07:58,498 --> 00:08:01,065
Once Hannah wakes up, we'll know
exactly what happened to her.

197
00:08:01,098 --> 00:08:02,465
My judgment is final.

198
00:08:02,498 --> 00:08:04,965
Now, robot, if you're really
as smart as they say,

199
00:08:04,998 --> 00:08:06,231
stay out of this.

200
00:08:06,265 --> 00:08:06,998
Mr. Chairman--
Please, wait!

201
00:08:09,498 --> 00:08:11,698
I can't believe
this is happening.

202
00:08:11,731 --> 00:08:13,098
DRAKE [ON TV]:
<i>This is just the beginning.</i>

203
00:08:13,131 --> 00:08:14,198
<i>Listen to me.</i>

204
00:08:14,231 --> 00:08:16,465
<i>All GP-IV model robots</i>
<i>have the capacity</i>

205
00:08:16,498 --> 00:08:18,065
<i>to turn against humans.</i>

206
00:08:18,098 --> 00:08:19,698
The next time,
it could be you.

207
00:08:19,731 --> 00:08:22,898
The GP-IVs appear to be
loyal workers to you and me,

208
00:08:22,931 --> 00:08:24,365
but behind their gentle faces,

209
00:08:24,398 --> 00:08:25,898
they harbor feelings
of anger and resentment

210
00:08:25,931 --> 00:08:27,731
toward all humans.

211
00:08:27,765 --> 00:08:29,931
<i>And just like Jake, they can</i>
<i>suddenly lash out at us</i>

212
00:08:29,965 --> 00:08:31,298
<i>at any time.</i>

213
00:08:31,331 --> 00:08:33,831
Mark my words.
These robots are lethal weapons.

214
00:08:33,865 --> 00:08:35,098
My baby!
Madam--

215
00:08:35,131 --> 00:08:36,098
Stay away!

216
00:08:36,131 --> 00:08:39,131
[♪]

217
00:08:48,765 --> 00:08:49,731
Reno?

218
00:08:49,765 --> 00:08:50,931
Astro.

219
00:08:50,965 --> 00:08:51,965
What did you wanna
show me?

220
00:08:51,998 --> 00:08:53,231
Take a look.

221
00:08:53,265 --> 00:08:55,831
ASTRO:
What's going on?

222
00:08:55,865 --> 00:08:57,731
RENO:
Rumors are flying
all over the city.

223
00:08:57,765 --> 00:08:59,465
People think the GP-IVs

224
00:08:59,498 --> 00:09:01,931
will revolt tonight in revenge
for what happened to Jake.

225
00:09:01,965 --> 00:09:03,265
Huh!
Who started that?

226
00:09:03,298 --> 00:09:04,165
I don't know.

227
00:09:04,198 --> 00:09:06,298
But now that Chairman Lyon
and Mr. Drake

228
00:09:06,331 --> 00:09:09,398
started working together,
no machine is safe.

229
00:09:09,431 --> 00:09:10,398
They won't stop

230
00:09:10,431 --> 00:09:13,231
until every robot in Metro City
is dismantled.

231
00:09:13,265 --> 00:09:15,231
[CROWD SHOUTING]

232
00:09:15,265 --> 00:09:16,331
[METAL CLATTERS]

233
00:09:17,398 --> 00:09:18,731
[CAT SCREECHES]

234
00:09:18,765 --> 00:09:20,831
Oh, no.

235
00:09:20,865 --> 00:09:22,465
[CHUCKLES]

236
00:09:22,498 --> 00:09:25,198
Like I've always said, a little
paranoia goes a long way.

237
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:28,831
Now, Kato, all we have to do
is stoke the fire.

238
00:09:28,865 --> 00:09:31,198
Yes, sir.
With pleasure.

239
00:09:31,231 --> 00:09:32,731
[EXPLOSION]

240
00:09:32,765 --> 00:09:35,765
[CROWD SHOUTING]

241
00:09:38,398 --> 00:09:40,865
[♪]

242
00:09:40,898 --> 00:09:43,331
It's the robots!

243
00:09:43,365 --> 00:09:44,731
He-- He's right!

244
00:09:44,765 --> 00:09:46,165
We've got you now.

245
00:09:46,198 --> 00:09:48,331
Let's destroy them!
Let's go!

246
00:09:48,365 --> 00:09:49,398
Yeah! Get them!

247
00:09:49,431 --> 00:09:50,965
This is bad, Astro.

248
00:09:50,998 --> 00:09:52,331
That mob
has got to be stopped.

249
00:09:52,365 --> 00:09:53,231
I'm on it!

250
00:09:55,098 --> 00:09:56,265
Don't let those robots
get away!

251
00:09:56,298 --> 00:09:58,698
Stop it!

252
00:09:58,731 --> 00:10:01,098
Leave them alone.
They didn't hurt you.

253
00:10:01,131 --> 00:10:03,198
Move it, Astro.
Stay out of our way.

254
00:10:03,231 --> 00:10:04,931
DELTA:
That's enough!

255
00:10:04,965 --> 00:10:07,098
You humans have caused
enough trouble for one night.

256
00:10:07,131 --> 00:10:09,198
You can't order us around.
You're just another robot.

257
00:10:09,231 --> 00:10:10,198
Come on. Let's go.

258
00:10:10,231 --> 00:10:10,965
[ASTRO GROANS]

259
00:10:12,398 --> 00:10:13,965
Aagh!

260
00:10:13,998 --> 00:10:15,865
You guys aren't
going anywhere.

261
00:10:15,898 --> 00:10:17,831
MAN:
Stop it, kid!

262
00:10:17,865 --> 00:10:19,231
MAN 2:
Whose side are you on anyway?

263
00:10:19,265 --> 00:10:20,865
Robots aren't the enemy.

264
00:10:20,898 --> 00:10:21,865
Come on, you.
Hey!

265
00:10:21,898 --> 00:10:23,831
Oh, hey!
Put me down!

266
00:10:23,865 --> 00:10:25,265
Oh, Reno!

267
00:10:25,298 --> 00:10:26,798
MAN:
Come on!
Let's go!

268
00:10:26,831 --> 00:10:28,198
[GROANING]

269
00:10:28,231 --> 00:10:30,198
Reno, are you okay?

270
00:10:30,231 --> 00:10:33,998
I tried to
stop them, Astro.

271
00:10:34,031 --> 00:10:35,298
I tried.

272
00:10:35,331 --> 00:10:36,931
Reno.

273
00:10:36,965 --> 00:10:39,398
Please help! We're trapped!
MAN: Ha-ha!

274
00:10:39,431 --> 00:10:40,865
We've got you now.

275
00:10:40,898 --> 00:10:42,465
We'll teach you robots
what happens

276
00:10:42,498 --> 00:10:44,231
when you mess
with humans.

277
00:10:44,265 --> 00:10:46,131
Yi-yaaagh!

278
00:10:46,165 --> 00:10:48,198
Stop!
Aaagh!

279
00:10:48,231 --> 00:10:49,198
Ugh!
Oh!

280
00:10:49,231 --> 00:10:50,298
Aaagh!

281
00:10:50,331 --> 00:10:51,698
Huh?

282
00:10:51,731 --> 00:10:53,331
What's that?
The Blue Knight.

283
00:10:53,365 --> 00:10:55,465
Now I will teach you
what happens

284
00:10:55,498 --> 00:10:56,731
when you mess with robots.

285
00:10:56,765 --> 00:10:57,731
Astro?

286
00:10:57,765 --> 00:10:59,198
Leave now.

287
00:10:59,231 --> 00:11:01,431
MAN:
Uh, guys? We gotta go!

288
00:11:01,465 --> 00:11:02,898
Blue Knight!

289
00:11:02,931 --> 00:11:04,898
Astro, why do you not

290
00:11:04,931 --> 00:11:06,698
use your powers
against the humans?

291
00:11:06,731 --> 00:11:08,398
How many innocent robots
must be destroyed

292
00:11:08,431 --> 00:11:10,931
before you see
that man is the enemy.

293
00:11:10,965 --> 00:11:11,931
[GASPS]

294
00:11:11,965 --> 00:11:13,998
BLUE KNIGHT:
Open your eyes.

295
00:11:14,031 --> 00:11:15,731
If you cannot fight
by my side,

296
00:11:15,765 --> 00:11:17,465
then you are nothing
but a traitor to me.

297
00:11:17,498 --> 00:11:19,898
[GROWLS]

298
00:11:19,931 --> 00:11:21,165
MEN:
We're under attack!

299
00:11:21,198 --> 00:11:22,831
Run!

300
00:11:24,165 --> 00:11:26,798
Now, what on earth
is going on here?

301
00:11:26,831 --> 00:11:29,198
SHADOW:
An age of change
is upon us.

302
00:11:29,231 --> 00:11:31,398
It's been a long time,
Dr. O'Shay.

303
00:11:31,431 --> 00:11:33,198
Uh, Shadow!

304
00:11:33,231 --> 00:11:35,698
<i>The robot scientist</i>
<i>created by Dr. Tenma!</i>

305
00:11:35,731 --> 00:11:36,965
<i>What are you doing here?</i>

306
00:11:36,998 --> 00:11:38,765
SHADOW:
<i>I'm the one who brought</i>
<i>the Blue Knight</i>

307
00:11:38,798 --> 00:11:39,965
<i>into this world.</i>

308
00:11:39,998 --> 00:11:41,431
Huh! It was you?

309
00:11:41,465 --> 00:11:42,765
SHADOW:
Yes.

310
00:11:42,798 --> 00:11:45,165
Under Dr. Tenma's orders.

311
00:11:45,198 --> 00:11:48,765
<i>He hoped the Blue Knight</i>
<i>would help Astro evolve.</i>

312
00:11:48,798 --> 00:11:50,265
<i>But instead, the Blue Knight</i>

313
00:11:50,298 --> 00:11:51,965
<i>started to follow</i>
<i>his own agenda.</i>

314
00:11:51,998 --> 00:11:54,098
His own agenda?

315
00:11:54,131 --> 00:11:56,198
SHADOW:
<i>The Blue Knight</i>
<i>believes in robots</i>

316
00:11:56,231 --> 00:11:58,131
<i>while Astro</i>
<i>believes in humans.</i>

317
00:11:58,165 --> 00:12:00,198
They will not stop

318
00:12:00,231 --> 00:12:02,298
until they've destroyed
each other

319
00:12:02,331 --> 00:12:04,831
and everything
around them.

320
00:12:23,765 --> 00:12:26,065
MALE NEWSCASTER: <i>In response to</i>
<i>last night's large-scale riot,</i>

321
00:12:26,098 --> 00:12:27,698
<i>the Federal Council</i>
<i>has issued a recall</i>

322
00:12:27,731 --> 00:12:29,031
<i>of all GP-IV model robots</i>

323
00:12:29,065 --> 00:12:30,231
<i>due to programming defects.</i>

324
00:12:30,265 --> 00:12:31,265
<i>In addition,</i>

325
00:12:31,298 --> 00:12:32,965
<i>the Council</i>
<i>has granted authorities</i>

326
00:12:32,998 --> 00:12:34,998
<i>the right to destroy</i>
<i>any GP-IV models</i>

327
00:12:35,031 --> 00:12:36,165
<i>that do not cooperate.</i>

328
00:12:36,198 --> 00:12:38,031
Huh! This is bad.

329
00:12:38,065 --> 00:12:41,865
Set a perimeter around the city
so no GP-IV robot can escape.

330
00:12:41,898 --> 00:12:43,731
Does everyone
understand?

331
00:12:43,765 --> 00:12:46,198
ALL:
Yes, sir!

332
00:12:46,231 --> 00:12:48,331
Delta, I'm putting you
in charge of this operation.

333
00:12:49,798 --> 00:12:51,431
I cannot...do this.

334
00:12:51,465 --> 00:12:53,465
That is an order.

335
00:12:53,498 --> 00:12:56,265
Now get to work.

336
00:13:03,231 --> 00:13:04,865
Detective!

337
00:13:04,898 --> 00:13:06,865
How could you
let this happen?

338
00:13:06,898 --> 00:13:08,898
Those robots haven't
done anything wrong.

339
00:13:08,931 --> 00:13:10,798
I thought
you'd understand.

340
00:13:10,831 --> 00:13:12,965
Astro, since your friend
the Blue Knight

341
00:13:12,998 --> 00:13:14,231
attacked those men
last night,

342
00:13:14,265 --> 00:13:15,898
the entire city
is up in arms.

343
00:13:15,931 --> 00:13:17,765
But it's just
not fair!

344
00:13:17,798 --> 00:13:18,831
There's no other way.

345
00:13:18,865 --> 00:13:20,031
I must do
whatever it takes

346
00:13:20,065 --> 00:13:22,131
to put the minds
of our citizens at ease.

347
00:13:22,165 --> 00:13:24,098
My only priority
right now

348
00:13:24,131 --> 00:13:25,898
is to make this city
safe again.

349
00:13:25,931 --> 00:13:26,898
[ASTRO SIGHS]

350
00:13:26,931 --> 00:13:28,898
Now, go home,
Astro.

351
00:13:28,931 --> 00:13:31,098
There's nothing
you can do here.

352
00:13:31,131 --> 00:13:34,198
You're wrong.
Robots have emotions too.

353
00:13:34,231 --> 00:13:35,965
Have you considered
their feelings?

354
00:13:35,998 --> 00:13:37,965
The GP-IVs
have done nothing wrong

355
00:13:37,998 --> 00:13:39,431
and now they face
being dismantled.

356
00:13:39,465 --> 00:13:40,965
And that's not all.

357
00:13:40,998 --> 00:13:42,931
What about the other robots
all over the city

358
00:13:42,965 --> 00:13:44,231
that have to stand by

359
00:13:44,265 --> 00:13:47,165
and watch their fellow
machines be destroyed?

360
00:13:47,198 --> 00:13:49,131
What about
their feelings?

361
00:13:49,165 --> 00:13:51,065
Have you thought about that,
Detective Tawashi?

362
00:13:51,098 --> 00:13:53,198
[GROANS]

363
00:14:04,398 --> 00:14:05,365
[CROWD MURMURING]

364
00:14:05,398 --> 00:14:07,231
If you ask me,
they're all evil.

365
00:14:07,265 --> 00:14:08,298
They're up to no good.

366
00:14:08,331 --> 00:14:10,965
Down to their very last bolt,
you can't trust them.

367
00:14:10,998 --> 00:14:11,898
That's the last
of them, sir.

368
00:14:26,365 --> 00:14:28,265
What's the matter?
They can't do anything right.

369
00:14:28,298 --> 00:14:30,165
Delta, you okay?

370
00:14:30,198 --> 00:14:31,365
DELTA:
I used to be proud

371
00:14:31,398 --> 00:14:33,731
to be the captain
of this squad.

372
00:14:33,765 --> 00:14:35,365
I used to think that
we protected a society

373
00:14:35,398 --> 00:14:37,831
in which both humans
and robots could live.

374
00:14:37,865 --> 00:14:40,931
But now, what
have we become,

375
00:14:40,965 --> 00:14:43,298
sending these robots
to their destruction?

376
00:14:43,331 --> 00:14:44,765
ROBOT:
Mr. Delta?

377
00:14:44,798 --> 00:14:47,431
We understand that
you are just doing your job.

378
00:14:47,465 --> 00:14:50,065
But if you refuse,
they will send you away

379
00:14:50,098 --> 00:14:52,231
to be destroyed
like the rest of us.

380
00:14:52,265 --> 00:14:54,731
So please,
close the container door.

381
00:14:54,765 --> 00:14:56,031
[GROWLS]

382
00:15:03,865 --> 00:15:07,165
Not a single defect can be found
in the GP-IV's programming.

383
00:15:07,198 --> 00:15:10,198
Chairman Lyon,
you're making a huge mistake.

384
00:15:10,231 --> 00:15:13,431
I beg you, please,
do not go through with this.

385
00:15:13,465 --> 00:15:15,265
You can beg
all you want, doctor,

386
00:15:15,298 --> 00:15:18,431
but I assure you
that it won't do any good.

387
00:15:24,465 --> 00:15:26,265
Reno!

388
00:15:26,298 --> 00:15:29,165
Reno?

389
00:15:29,198 --> 00:15:30,465
Huh?

390
00:15:30,498 --> 00:15:32,298
This is the same hospital
where Hannah's staying.

391
00:15:32,331 --> 00:15:33,898
Huh! Reno.

392
00:15:38,765 --> 00:15:40,298
[DOOR OPENS]

393
00:15:40,331 --> 00:15:41,831
Reno.

394
00:15:41,865 --> 00:15:44,431
I wish Hannah
would wake up

395
00:15:44,465 --> 00:15:46,265
and tell everybody
what really happened.

396
00:15:46,298 --> 00:15:48,331
RENO:
Things have changed so much

397
00:15:48,365 --> 00:15:50,198
in the last
couple of days

398
00:15:50,231 --> 00:15:53,431
At least in her dreams,
she's still with Jake.

399
00:15:53,465 --> 00:15:56,098
Astro, are things ever
gonna be the same again?

400
00:16:04,098 --> 00:16:05,231
REPORTER:
As you can see,

401
00:16:05,265 --> 00:16:08,698
the defective GP-IV model
robots are being transported

402
00:16:08,731 --> 00:16:10,698
to a robot dismantling plant
just outside of Metro City.

403
00:16:10,731 --> 00:16:12,031
[GROWLS]

404
00:16:12,065 --> 00:16:13,231
WOMAN: Yeah!
MAN: Take them apart.

405
00:16:13,265 --> 00:16:14,698
WOMAN:
We don't need them.

406
00:16:14,731 --> 00:16:16,098
Get rid of them.

407
00:16:16,131 --> 00:16:17,098
MAN:
Get those robots
outta here.

408
00:16:17,131 --> 00:16:18,865
WOMAN:
Do it!

409
00:16:34,231 --> 00:16:36,098
My only priority
right now

410
00:16:36,131 --> 00:16:37,331
is to make this city
safe again.

411
00:16:37,365 --> 00:16:39,931
Astro, you are nothing
but a traitor to me.

412
00:16:51,331 --> 00:16:52,298
[BRAKES SQUEAL]

413
00:16:55,065 --> 00:16:56,698
Huh?

414
00:16:56,731 --> 00:16:57,931
TAWASHI:
Astro?

415
00:16:57,965 --> 00:16:59,831
I can't let you
do this, general.

416
00:16:59,865 --> 00:17:01,465
Until now,
humans and robots

417
00:17:01,498 --> 00:17:03,265
have been able
to live together in peace.

418
00:17:03,298 --> 00:17:04,698
Astro--

419
00:17:04,731 --> 00:17:06,331
ASTRO:
But this will change everything.

420
00:17:06,365 --> 00:17:08,298
Can't you see this is wrong?

421
00:17:08,331 --> 00:17:09,798
Don't stop.

422
00:17:09,831 --> 00:17:10,798
General! Astro--

423
00:17:10,831 --> 00:17:12,431
I said don't stop!

424
00:17:12,465 --> 00:17:14,331
[ENGINE ROARING]

425
00:17:15,731 --> 00:17:16,998
[ASTRO GASPS]

426
00:17:17,031 --> 00:17:18,898
[GRUNTING]

427
00:17:21,065 --> 00:17:22,031
Astro!

428
00:17:22,065 --> 00:17:24,131
Riot Squad, come in.
Do you copy?

429
00:17:24,165 --> 00:17:26,065
GENERAL [OVER RADIO]:
Destroy Astro!

430
00:17:27,331 --> 00:17:28,998
Aaagh!

431
00:17:30,131 --> 00:17:31,098
[GASPS]

432
00:17:31,131 --> 00:17:32,731
ASTRO:
It's the Blue Knight.

433
00:17:32,765 --> 00:17:34,198
Ha!

434
00:17:34,231 --> 00:17:36,831
Whatever you do,
don't let them take the GP-IVs.

435
00:17:43,131 --> 00:17:45,898
Aaagh!

436
00:17:45,931 --> 00:17:47,165
The Blue Knight
has struck again,

437
00:17:47,198 --> 00:17:48,231
attacking the trucks

438
00:17:48,265 --> 00:17:50,865
<i>carrying the captured</i>
<i>GP-IV robots.</i>

439
00:17:50,898 --> 00:17:52,198
BLUE KNIGHT:
<i>My fellow machines,</i>

440
00:17:52,231 --> 00:17:55,098
<i>let us rise up</i>
<i>against the humans</i>

441
00:17:55,131 --> 00:17:56,965
<i>and finally be free.</i>

442
00:18:00,898 --> 00:18:03,265
Delta, don't just
stand there.

443
00:18:03,298 --> 00:18:06,031
Aaagh!

444
00:18:07,398 --> 00:18:09,231
Say goodbye, humans.

445
00:18:09,265 --> 00:18:10,431
Blue Knight!

446
00:18:13,465 --> 00:18:14,965
[GROANING]

447
00:18:16,298 --> 00:18:18,065
Astro!
Blue Knight!

448
00:18:18,098 --> 00:18:19,365
You cannot hurt them.

449
00:18:19,398 --> 00:18:21,231
I will show you
no more mercy.

450
00:18:21,265 --> 00:18:22,431
[GASPS]

451
00:18:22,465 --> 00:18:24,031
Aaagh! Aaagh! Aaagh!

452
00:18:28,298 --> 00:18:29,398
Detective,
what's happening?

453
00:18:29,431 --> 00:18:30,165
They've got
the trucks.

454
00:18:32,231 --> 00:18:34,365
[GROANING]

455
00:18:34,398 --> 00:18:37,131
Tonight, we take control
of our destiny.

456
00:18:37,165 --> 00:18:38,265
Tonight,
we are free.

457
00:18:38,298 --> 00:18:40,831
BLUE KNIGHT [ON TV]:
<i>Robots everywhere, unite.</i>

458
00:18:40,865 --> 00:18:43,698
The revolution
has begun.

459
00:18:48,898 --> 00:18:50,031
Huh?
Aah!

460
00:18:50,065 --> 00:18:51,231
Aagh! Robots!

461
00:18:59,465 --> 00:19:01,898
Ugh! Blue Knight!

462
00:19:01,931 --> 00:19:04,865
[MOANING]

463
00:19:06,365 --> 00:19:08,365
[GASPS]

464
00:19:08,398 --> 00:19:09,365
Where am I?

465
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:10,365
It's a miracle.

466
00:19:10,398 --> 00:19:12,231
You woke up.

467
00:19:12,265 --> 00:19:13,631
I'll get the doctor.

468
00:19:13,665 --> 00:19:17,131
POLICE BULLETIN:
<i>Robots have rebelled</i>
<i>against humans.</i>

469
00:19:17,165 --> 00:19:18,465
<i>For your safety,</i>
<i>stay inside</i>

470
00:19:18,498 --> 00:19:20,998
<i>and lock your doors</i>
<i>and windows.</i>

471
00:19:23,065 --> 00:19:24,298
Robots?

472
00:19:24,331 --> 00:19:25,298
Jake?

473
00:19:25,331 --> 00:19:26,265
It can't be.

474
00:19:27,498 --> 00:19:29,398
Hannah, you're awake.

475
00:19:29,431 --> 00:19:31,165
What happened?

476
00:19:31,198 --> 00:19:33,898
Do you know Jake?
Where is he?

477
00:19:33,931 --> 00:19:35,831
Hannah...

478
00:19:35,865 --> 00:19:37,165
Jake.

479
00:19:37,198 --> 00:19:38,098
Jake!

480
00:19:38,131 --> 00:19:39,131
POLICE BULLETIN:
<i>The Federal Council</i>

481
00:19:39,165 --> 00:19:42,065
<i>has declared</i>
<i>a state of emergency.</i>

482
00:19:42,098 --> 00:19:47,131
All robots should be considered
<i>armed and dangerous.</i>

483
00:19:50,798 --> 00:19:52,765
[♪]

